  "text": "Fitbit Sense 2 $189 $250 Save $61 Case Material Aluminum Case size 40mm Colors Graphite, Platinum, Soft Gold Display 1.6\" OLED Battery 6+ days (AOD off); 2 to 3 days (AOD on) If you're looking to track your health and fitness metrics and want something easy to use, the Fitbit Sense 2 is going to be a fantastic option. For a limited time, you can grab this smartwatch at its best price. It's the last few hours to save before Prime Day comes to a close. And if you're looking for a no-nonsense smartwatch that's aimed at tracking health and fitness metrics, the Fitbit Sense 2 is going to be right up your alley. Sure, you can probably spring for a Galaxy or Pixel Watch, but this one delivers over six days of battery life on a single charge, which is extremely convenient. What's great about the Fitbit Sense 2? Slim, stylish, and battery that can last up to a week with light use. The Fitbit Sense 2 was one of those devices that was just too expensive to love when it was first released. Luckily, the price has come down, and is now at its lowest at just $189, which makes it worth looking at. The watch features a 1.6-inch OLED screen and has sensors that track heart rate, SpO2, skin temperature, and more. The Sense 2 will be able to give you a great overview of your health, along with data about your stress and sleep quality too. You aren't going to have access to new apps like a traditional Wear OS smartwatch, but everything you need to track your health and fitness activities is already on the watch, which means there's less to worry about. In our review, we liked the experience, and it is an excellent piece of hardware. So, if health tracking is your main goal with a wearable, this is going to be a great option to go with.",
