al banner from Android Police\" src=\"https://static0.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/img_0103.png\"/\u003e\n \u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003ch2 id=\"what-39-s-great-about-the-fitbit-sense-2\"\u003e\n                        What\u0026#39;s great about the Fitbit Sense 2?\n               \u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\n\n    \n\n\n\n                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                \n    \n\u003cp\u003eSlim, stylish, and battery that can last up to a week with light use. The Fitbit Sense 2 was one of those devices that was just too expensive to love when it was first released. Luckily, the price has come down, and is now at its lowest at just $189, which makes it worth looking at. \u003c/p\u003e    \u003cp\u003eThe watch features a 1.6-inch OLED screen and has sensors that track heart rate, SpO2, skin temperature, and more. The Sense 2 will be able to give you a great overview of your health, along with data about your stress and sleep quality too. \u003c/p\u003e    \u003cp\u003eYou aren\u0026#39;t going to have access to new apps like a traditional Wear OS smartwatch, but everything you need to track your health and fitness activities is already on the watch, which means there\u0026#39;s less to worry about.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003cp\u003eIn \u003ca href=\"https://www.androidpolice.com/fitbit-sense-2-review/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eour review\u003c/a\u003e, we liked the experience, and it is an excellent piece of hardware. So, if health tracking is your main goal with a wearable, this is going to be a great option to go with. \u003c/p\u003e    \u003c/div\u003e\n    \n                \n        \n        \n\n\n        \n\n\n\n\n\n                                            \n\n\n\n\n        \n    \u003c/article\u003e\n\n    \n            \n        \u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
